subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis . Telson anterolateral margin with smooth proximal concavity over anterior 70 % that ends at sharp step, remainder truncate-convex, margin oblique anterior to transverse suture, with crenellate margin. Pereopods 2–4 with dactyli 5.9–6.2 times as long as greatest basal width, robust setae on dactylus of pereopod 2 number 7–26 (median 12 ), of pereopod 3, 1– 10 (median 3 ), and of pereopod 4 , 0–6 (median 2 ). Pereopod 4 merus without spines proximally on upper face. (revised from
Poore & Andreakis 2012
)
